<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--SunnyLondon     05-09 0070</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Sunny London,0069</SECOND>
<HEAD>What London Fog? Sunniest Week In Nearly Three Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   That unfamiliar object seen in London's sky last
week was the sun, putting in its longest appearance in nearly three
years.
   The London Weather Center reported Monday that the city had 64.8
hours of sunshine last week. That was the most since June 1986,
when the sun was out for 75.9 hours one week.
</TEXT>
