<HEAD>`K-9' Nips `Pet Sematary' For No. 1 Spot</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICHARD DE ATLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``K-9,'' the cop and dog movie, nipped previous
leader ``Pet Sematary'' for first place in the nation's weekend box
office, while ``Field of Dreams'' added screens to slide in at
third.
   ``K-9,'' starring Jim Belushi, took in $6.44 million, while
``Pet Sematary'' earned $6.3 million, according to figures released
Monday by Exhibitor Relations Co.
   ``Field of Dreams,'' a fantasy movie about resurrection,
redemption and baseball, added 523 screens to jump to No. 3,
earning $5.4 million.
   The baseball comedy ``Major League'' sold $3.5 million in
tickets for fourth place, followed by ``Criminal Law'' with $1.9
million.
   ``Listen To Me,'' a film about a high school debating team
taking on the issue of abortion, had a weak debut at $1.78 million.
``The Dream Team'' took in $1.75 million for seventh place and
``Say Anything'' earned $1.6 million for eighth.
   In ninth place was ``Rain Man,'' with $1.5 million, while
``Scandal,'' the movie about the Profumo affair that rocked Britain
in 1963, was in 10th place with more than $980,000.
   Here are the top movies for the weekend as tallied by Exhibitor
Relations, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater
screens, average per screen, total gross and number of weeks in
release.
   1. ``K-9,'' Universal, $6.4 million, 1,700 screens, $3,790 per
screen, $15.9 million, two weeks.
   2. ``Pet Sematary,'' Paramount, $6.3 million, 1,585 screens,
$3,999 per screen, $33.2 million, three weeks.
   3. ``Field of Dreams,'' Universal, $5.4 million, 633 screens,
$8,570 per screen, $8.3 million, three weeks.
   4. ``Major League,'' Paramount, $3.5 million, 1,557 screens,
$2,308 per screen, $35.9 million, five weeks.
   5. ``Criminal Law,'' Hemdale, $1.92 million, 1,122 screens,
$1,712 per screen, $5.3 million, two weeks.
   6. ``Listen To Me,'' Weintraub Entertainment Group, $1.78
million, 1,306 screens, $1,370 per screen, $1.78 million, one week.
   7. ``The Dream Team,'' Universal, $1.75 million, 1,233 screens,
$1,425 per screen, $21.4 million, five weeks.
   8. ``Say Anything,'' 20th Century Fox, $1.6 million, 1,024
screens, $1,640 per screen, $14.5 million, four weeks.
   9. ``Rain Man,'' MGM-UA, $1.5 million, 1,218 screens, $1,302 per
screen, $160 million, 21 weeks.
   10. ``Scandal,'' Miramax, $981,150, 214 screens, $4,584 per
screen, $1.8 million, two weeks.
