<FIRST>r a PM-ImpostorAstronaut     05-09 0261</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Impostor Astronaut,0265</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fake Astronaut Sentenced for Credit Card Fraud</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who claimed to be an astronaut pleaded
guilty to using his wife's company-issued credit card to charter a
jet. He was ordered to undergo a psychiatric evaluation as part of
his sentence.
   Robert Hunt, 27, also was sentenced Monday to three months and
12 days in the Suffolk County House of Correction, the time he has
already served in the jail since his arrest Jan. 28.
   Municipal Court Judge Herbert Hershfang also ordered Hunt to pay
the air charter company $5,994. He chartered a jet last summer to
fly with his wife to Montreal, charging it on her credit card while
telling her the flight cost nothing because he was a space shuttle
pilot, authorities said.
   Hunt's plea was part of an agreement with the district
attorney's office. Hunt was placed on probation for one year and
ordered to complete any program ordered by a court psychiatrist.
   Authorities said Hunt has posed as an astronaut, Marine captain,
jet pilot and building contractor.
   He reportedly posed as an astronaut in a brief meeting with
Benjamin Briscoe, Dublin's lord mayor, while in Ireland. He also is
reported to have lectured aviation buffs in Bedford and to have
given friends and relatives burned kitchen tiles, saying they came
from the wreck of the space shuttle Challenger.
   Hunt was released Monday but faces a charge in Lynn District
Court of swindling a family out of $4,000 on the promise he could
get their 18-year-old son out of the Navy.
</TEXT>
