<FIRST>u i PM-Australia-Hostages     05-09 0135</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Australia-Hostages,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gunman Storms Kindergarten, Takes Children Hostage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman stormed a kindergarten
today, doused four children with gasoline and threatened to set
them on fire. He later surrendered to police, a news agency
reported.
   The gunman gave himself up after a seven-hour standoff at the
Manresa kindergarten in Melbourne, the Australian Associated Press
reported. Four children were released unharmed.
   The man, a Turkish national identified as Serafettin Huseyin,
32, forced the 4-year-old children inside a bathroom stall, doused
them with gasoline and threatened to set them on fire, AAP said.
   The news agency said the man was demanding action on a long
dispute he had with a hospital over treatment given his wife.
   AAP said the man gave himself up after speaking with his wife
and a television reporter.
</TEXT>
