<SECOND>AM-BRF--Misfortune,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fortune Tellers' Crystal Balls Stolen; They Didn't See it Coming</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five fortune tellers from northern
England said Tuesday they had to abandon a tour of Ireland because
their crystal balls were stolen.
   Margaret Pickering said members of the group sensed something
might go wrong soon after they arrived in Ireland.
   ``We were aware something was about to happen, but we did not
know what,'' said Mrs. Pickering, a medium from Hull. ``We did not
think our luggage might be taken.''
   The crystal balls, tarot cards and other essential tools of the
clairvoyants' trade were taken from their car while it was parked
outside a guest house in Dublin.
   Irish police said they were investigating the theft.
   ``Just what the thieves will do with their haul remains a
mystery,'' a spokesman said. ``You might say we are looking into it
... if only we had a crystal ball to help us.''
