<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--MoneyChase     05-09 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Money Chase,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Robbery Suspect Tosses Money from Car During Police Chase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUSTIN, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A suspected bank robber tossed handfuls of
cash from his car while police chased him on a freeway, then
ditched the car and ran into a store in an unsuccessful attempt to
hide, police said.
   The man climbed into an attic crawl space that couldn't hold his
weight.
   ``The (store) employee heard a big thud upstairs. She looked up
over a balcony and saw a guy's head,'' police Lt. Frank
Semelsberger said Monday.
   The frightened employee at the Discoveries jewelry and craft
gallery fled the store, Semelsberger said, and police moved in with
a dog.
   Eric Raymond Martin, 22, of San Diego, surrendered at first
sight of the dog and was booked for investigation of robbery, he
said.
   Martin allegedly robbed Far West Savings And Loan Association,
then drove away on the traffic-clogged Costa Mesa Freeway, tossing
money frm his car as police followed, said Semelsberger.
   Sgt. Bill Fisher said Tuesday that less than $4,000 was taken
from Far West and all but about $800 had been recovered.
</TEXT>
