<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An elevator fell nine stories after
its cables snapped Tuesday, killing six construction workers and
injuring four, authorities said.
   The elevator was on the 14th floor of a 28-story condominium
being built in Manila when the cables broke, and the car crashed to
the fifth floor, witnesses said.
   One man was crushed by the elevator when he peered into the
shaft upon hearing the shouts of fellow workers.
   It was not known what caused the cables to break or how many
people were in the elevator when the accident happened.
   Four workers died at the scene and two others died later,
officials said.
