<HEAD>Bush Taps Herres for Another Term as Vice Chairman of Joint Chiefs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush has nominated Air Force Gen.
Robert T. Herres, 56, a native of Denver, to serve a second
two-year term as the vice chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff,
the Pentagon said Tuesday.
   Herres is the first officer to hold that post, created through a
major Pentagon reorganization initiative approved by Congress in
1986. His reappointment requires Senate confirmation.
