<HEAD>Army Reports 27 Guerrillas Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 27 communist guerrillas were
killed in several battles over the previous 24 hours, a policeman
and a civilian were slain and 18 soldiers were wounded, the
military reported Tuesday.
   In the bloodiest confrontation, soldiers attacked a New People's
Army encampment at dusk Monday in the mountain town of Vintar in
Ilocos Norte province 250 miles north of Manila, army headquarters
reported.
   Members of the First Scout Ranger Regiment had been monitoring
rebel activity in Vintar for weeks and decided to attack after
identifying the guerrilla positions, the report said.
   At least nine rebels were killed and two captured in sporadic
clashes that continued Tuesday, and eight soldiers were wounded,
the army reported.
