<HEAD>RJR Nabisco To Sell Five European Foods Units</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   RJR Nabisco Inc. said Tuesday it plans to auction
five European foods businesses as part of an effort to reduce debt
following the $24.53 billion takeover by the investment firm
Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co.
   The businesses include the British biscuits business of Nabisco
and two British potato chip and snacks makers, Walker's Crisps and
Smiths Crisps.
   The company said it also intends to sell its French cookie and
specialty pastries maker, Belin Group, and Saiwa, an Italian
biscuit and snacks maker.
   RJR Nabisco, which intends to reduce debt by $5.5 billion
through sales of some subsidiaries, said it already has been
approached by numerous firms about the European businesses.
   Together, the five units had pretax profit of $137 million on
sales of $1.2 billion in 1988.
   ``Each of these businesses is highly attractive,'' R.E. Glover,
president of the International Nabisco Brands division, said in a
statement.
