<HEAD>GAF First Quarter Earnings Up 12 Percent Over Same Period Last Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAYNE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GAF Corp. announced Tuesday its earnings rose
12 percent in the first quarter, its last quarter as a public
company.
   Net income for the first quarter totaled $25.4 million, or 91
cents per share, up from $22.7 million, or 79 cents per share, in
the first three months of 1988.
   Earnings rose in the latest quarter despite $31.5 million in
charges resulting from the March 29 purchase of the company by a
group of GAF executives led by Chairman Samuel J. Heyman.
   GAF, a leading manufacturer of specialty chemicals and building
materials, reported total first-quarter sales of $239.3 million, up
from $216.5 in the same period the previous year.
   The company's chemicals business registered its highest
quarterly sales and profits ever, with profits up 27 percent from
$35 million last year to $44 milion, and sales up from $128.6
million to $152 million.
